quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  23,93,"Say, \"My Lord! if you should show me what they are promised"
  23,94,My Lord! Then place me not amongst the wrong-doing people
  23,95,And verily We are able to show you that which We have promised them
  23,96,Repel evil by that which is best. We are best Aware of that which they allege
  23,97,"And say, \"My Lord! I seek refuge in Thee from the suggestions of the devils"
  23,98,And I seek refuge in Thee from their presence
  23,99,"Until when death comes to any one of them he says, \"My Lord! Send me back"
  23,100,"That I may do right in that which I have left behind.\" Nay! It is but a mere word he speaks; behind them is a barrier until the Day they shall be raised"
  23,101,"And when the trumpet shall be blown, and there shall be no kinship between them on that day, nor will they ask about each other then"
  23,102,"And those whose scales are heavy (with good deeds), they are the successful"
  23,103,"But those whose scales are light, these are they who lose their souls, in hell will they abide"
  23,104,"The fire shall scorch their faces, and they shall curl their lips (in gloom) therein"
  23,105,"(It will be said) \"Were not My revelations recited to you? And did you not treat them as falsehoods"
  23,106,"They will say, \"Our Lord our misfortune overcame us, and we became a people astray"
  23,107,"Our Lord! Take us out of this, and if we return to evil, then shall we be unjust indeed"
  23,108,"He will say, \"Be gone into it, and speak you not to Me"
  23,109,"Verily, there was a sect of My servants who used to pray, \"Our Lord! We believe, so forgive us, and have mercy upon us, for Thou art the best of the merciful ones"
  23,110,But you took them for a jest (treated them with ridicule) until you forgot My reminder and did laugh at them
  23,111,"Verily, I have rewarded them this day that they were steadfast; verily, they are indeed triumphant, blissful now"
  23,112,"He will say, \"How long a number of years did you tarry on earth"
  23,113,"They will say, \"We tarried but a day or part of a day, but ask those who keep count"
  23,114,"He will say, \"You have only tarried a little, if you but knew"
  23,115,"Did you then think that We created you for jest (or sport, without purpose), and that you would not be returned to Us"
  23,116,"But exalted be Allah, the True King; there is no God but He, the Lord of the Noble Throne (or Throne of Honour)"
  23,117,"He who calls unto any other God along with Allah has no proof thereof; verily, his account is only with his Lord; verily, the disbelievers shall not be successful"
  23,118,"And say, \"Lord, Forgive and have mercy, for you are the best of the merciful ones"